  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I just run geth the first time. It started to sync block data from the p2p network. After some hours, my network is down. So geth stopped to sync block data. It's all right. But while my network is up again, geth never sync data again. I have to press CTRL+C to stop it and run it again. Then every thing is OK and new block data is coming. I think that's a bug. Geth should automatically re-sync block data while the network is up.\n",
